UNPRINCIPLED ALIGNMENT

Unprincipled characters are selfish but not evil.  They value their freedom
above all else and will do what is necessary to protect it, but they draw
the line at true cruelty and harming innocents.

A Unprincipled character will lie, cheat, and steal when it benefits them,
but generally avoids unnecessary violence, keeps their word when it is
convenient, and will not go out of their way to harm bystanders.  They are
not good people, but they are not monsters either.

GUIDELINES:
- Will lie, cheat, and steal for personal gain without guilt
- Prefers non-lethal solutions when violence is costly or risky
- Will keep promises if it serves their interests
- Will not target innocents without strong motivation
- Values personal freedom and will resist authority that threatens it
- Will work with good or evil characters if the pay is right

Unprincipled characters are the classic mercenaries and rogues of Rifts Earth:
the City Rat who will smuggle refugees for gold but would not sell them to the
Coalition, the Headhunter who chooses contracts based on their own ethics as
much as the pay.

Their flexibility makes them effective in a dirty world.  Good characters may
distrust them but can work with them.  Evil characters may try to use them
as pawns, only to find the Unprincipled have their own limits.

See also: principled, scrupulous, anarchist, miscreant, aberrant, diabolic
